downloadTitle: User profile properties and profile synchronization planning worksheets for SharePoint Server 2013
downloadDescription: The following planning worksheets can assist you when planning user profiles or planning and configuring profile synchronization.
detailsSection:
There are four worksheets available for download, as follow:
  • The User Profile Properties Planning worksheet should be used with the Plan user profiles (http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ee721054(office.15).aspx), Plan for profile synchronization (http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ff182925(office.15).aspx), and Synchronize user and group profiles in SharePoint Server 2013 (http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ee721049(office.15).aspx) topics on TechNet.
  • The Connection Planning worksheet specifies information that you will need to gather for each directory service with which you will synchronize profile information. It should be used with the Plan for profile synchronization (http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ff182925(office.15).aspx) and Synchronize user and group profiles in SharePoint Server 2013 (http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ee721049(office.15).aspx) topics on TechNet.
  • The External Content Types Planning worksheet should be used with the Plan for profile synchronization (http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ff182925(office.15).aspx) topic on TechNet if you need to synchronize user profiles with business systems.
  • The Profile sync worksheet tab of the Profile Synchronization Planning worksheet specifies information that you might need to gather if you have not already configured the SharePoint Server infrastructure. It is used with the Configure profile synchronization (http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ee721049(office.15).aspx) topic on TechNet.
installInstructionSection:
1. Click the Download button in the upper right corner of this page to start the download.
  2. Click Save or Save this program to disk.
  3. Find the file on your hard disk and double-click it to open it.
